title: Led Zeppelin - 1977.05.26 Landover, Maryland
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1977.05.26 Landover, Maryland   

MAGIK KINGDOM 
DOUBLE SHOT II (6CD BOX)
Empress Valley EVSD-574~579
Limited to 100 copies

[Sbd Recording at Capitol Center, 
Landover, MD, USA, 26th May 1977] 

Source: 
Incomplete excellent soundboard recording. Almost 181 minutes.
(some audience patching)

Details: 
The recording is a very good balanced professional board tape from house mix.

Tracklist:

01. The Song Remains The Same 
02. The Rover intro / Sick Again 
03. Nobody's Fault But Mine 
04. In My Time of Dying 
05. Since I've Been Loving You 
06. No Quarter 

Disc 2: 
01. Ten Years Gone 
02. Battle of Evermore 
03. Going to California 
04. Dancing Days 
05. Black Country Woman 
06. Bron-Y-Aur Stomp 
07. White Summer/Black Mountain Side 
08. Kashmir 

Disc 3: 
01. Out On the Tiles intro / Moby Dick 
02. Jimmy Page Solo 
03. Achilles Last Stand 
04. Stairway to Heaven 
05. Whole Lotta Love 
06. Rock and Roll

Comments: 
Another strong accent. Since I've Been Loving You is very powerful, 
No Quarter an epic and Ten Years Gone is also excellent. A great, 
short, impromptu version of Dancing Days leads into Black Country 
Woman. Moby Dick for drum solo fans is over 35 minutes long here! 
So sad Jimmy not goes deeper into Communication Breakdown but only 
teasing the audience with a riff
